The template is continuously checked for correct syntax. If there are syntax errors, e.g. dynamic elements whose XPath expression cannot be resolved, or if linked files such as collections or images cannot be found, these errors are displayed in the verification view. You can toggle the view on and off with the ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon.

The messages can be clicked on and the corresponding element will be marked in the outline. The errors are also marked with a small icon directly in the outline. If you move the mouse over the corresponding element in the outline, the error message is displayed.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Text element validation
Text elements have the property "validation-pattern". This property can be used in the Business Designer during template creation to check whether the entered text corresponds to a defined specification. The property can contain a text entered as a string but also a regex (regular expression). If only a string/text is entered, it is checked whether the validation- pattern value matches the text from the editor. If it matches, no warning is issued, if it does not match, a warning is displayed. Example: If in the editor "correct text" was entered and the input validation-pattern also contains the value "correct text", then no warning appears in the validation window. As soon as one of the two values is changed, the warning that the text does not match appears. With this function it can be indicated on the one hand that a text does not correspond to an exact pattern, on the other hand the opposite can be achieved by means of Regex, for example the text must be changed in order to remove the warning. An example for this regex is:

(^(?!\s*$))(^(?!Insert text here.$).*) If the editor now says exactly "Insert text here." a warning appears:
